In order to capture debug messages from [Oracle&#39;s SSL implementation](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/security/oracle-providers.html#GUID-7093246A-31A3-4304-AC5F-5FB6400405E2) you need:

 1. Configure it to use a proper logging API instead of `System.out`,
 2. Use a logging layout that allows for multiline messages.

Redirect SunJSEE debug
----------------------

Since Java 8, SunJSSE can use a proper logging API if you set the `javax.net.debug` variable to an **empty** string, e.g. with `-Djavax.net.debug=`. The actual logging API depends on the Java version:

 * Java 8 uses `java.util.logging`. You&#39;ll need [`log4j-jul`](https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/log4j-jul.html) to forward it to the Log4j 2.x API,
 * Java 9 and later uses [`System.Logger`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/9/docs/api/java/lang/System.Logger.html). You&#39;ll need [`log4j-jpl`](https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/log4j-jpl.html) to forward it to the Log4j 2.x API. Alternatively `System.Logger` binds by default to `java.util.logging`.

Change logging layout
---------------------

To easily import your SunJSSE logs into Graylog you probably want to use a GELF layout. Your `log4j2-spring.xml` file would look like this:

```lang-xml
&lt;Configuration name=&quot;app&quot; status=&quot;WARN&quot;&gt;
  &lt;Appenders&gt;
    &lt;File name=&quot;FILE&quot; fileName=&quot;${sys:LOG_FILE}&quot;&gt;
      &lt;JsonTemplateLayout eventTemplateUri=&quot;classpath:GelfLayout.json&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/File&gt;
  &lt;/Appenders&gt;
  &lt;Loggers&gt;
    &lt;Root level=&quot;INFO&quot;&gt;
      &lt;AppenderRef ref=&quot;FILE&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/Root&gt;
    &lt;Logger name=&quot;javax.net.ssl&quot; level=&quot;DEBUG&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;/Loggers&gt;
&lt;/Configuration&gt;
```

(you need [`log4j-layout-json-template`](https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/json-template-layout.html) for this).

Alternatively you can use an [RFC5424 layout](https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/layouts.html#RFC5424Layout) and escape the new lines:

```lang-xml
&lt;Configuration name=&quot;app&quot; status=&quot;WARN&quot;&gt;
  &lt;Appenders&gt;
    &lt;File name=&quot;FILE&quot; fileName=&quot;${sys:LOG_FILE}&quot;&gt;
      &lt;Rfc5424Layout newLine=&quot;true&quot; newLineEscape=&quot; &quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/File&gt;
  &lt;/Appenders&gt;
  &lt;Loggers&gt;
    &lt;Root level=&quot;INFO&quot;&gt;
      &lt;AppenderRef ref=&quot;FILE&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/Root&gt;
    &lt;Logger name=&quot;javax.net.ssl&quot; level=&quot;DEBUG&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;/Loggers&gt;
&lt;/Configuration&gt;
```

